Formosa Petrochemical, Ruentex Industries: Taiwan Stocks Preview

-- B y   W e i y i   L i m
-- 
2011-08-04T00:54:51Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-04/formosa-petrochemical-ruentex-industries-taiwan-stocks-preview.html
Shares of the following companies may
have unusual moves in  Taiwan  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the last close in Taipei.  The Taiex Index fell 127.86, or 1.5 percent, to 8,456.86.  Formosa Petrochemical Corp. (6505)  (6505 TT): Taiwan’s only
publicly traded oil refiner is asking other Asian refiners to
take delivery of crude supplies it can’t process after the
shutdown of its Mailiao plant because of a fire, according to
three people with knowledge of the talks. Lin Keh-yen, a Taipei-
based company spokesman, declined to comment on the talks. The
stock slipped 0.1 percent to NT$93.90.  Ruentex Industries Ltd. (2915)  (2915 TT): The textile company
plans to sell 130 million new shares at NT$54 each, the company
said in a statement to the Taiwan stock exchange yesterday. It
plans to raise NT$7.02 billion ($243 million) from the offer to
inject funds in venture Ruen Chen Investment Holdings Co., the
company said. The stock retreated 3.9 percent to NT$68.70.  United Microelectronics Corp. (2303)  (2303 TT): The world’s
second-largest contract maker of chips, said second-quarter net
income fell 39 percent to NT$3.19 billion, the Hsinchu, Taiwan-
based company said in a statement yesterday. The average of 10
analyst estimates compiled by Bloomberg was for profit of
NT$3.58 billion. The stock lost 1.2 percent to NT$12.65.  WT Microelectronics Co. (3036 TT): The integrated circuit
maker will acquire  Techmosa International Inc. (3389)  (3389 TT), a
distributor of semiconductor products, in a share swap, the
Taiwan stock exchange said in a text message yesterday. WT added
0.2 percent to NT$56.30. Techmosa decreased 3.6 percent to
NT$29.90.  To contact the reporter on this story:
